Tyler Milligan is a name that resonates with fans of rodeo, particularly those who follow the sport of tie-down roping. Born and raised in Pawhuska, Oklahoma, Milligan has made a name for himself in the world of professional rodeo, showcasing his skills in the arena and earning recognition as a three-time Wrangler National Finals Rodeo Qualifier. 

Here we have Tyler Milligan’s net worth, career earnings, professional career, relationship status, and more.

About Tyler Milligan

Tyler Milligan was born and raised in Pawhuska, Oklahoma. His love for rodeo was instilled in him from a young age, as he grew up on a ranch where his father and grandfather were also involved in the sport. Milligan’s early exposure to rodeo and his family’s influence played a significant role in shaping his career path.

Despite being homeschooled, Milligan had the opportunity to compete in rodeo at the high school level, where he also participated in team roping. In his junior year of high school, he won the national championship in team roping. 

However, as he grew older, Milligan decided to focus on calf roping, a decision that would set the stage for his professional career.

Early Life

Growing up on a ranch, Milligan was exposed to the world of rodeo from a young age. His father and grandfather were both involved in the sport, and their influence played a significant role in shaping his career path.

Despite being homeschooled, Milligan had the opportunity to compete in rodeo at the high school level, where he also participated in team roping. In his junior year of high school, he won the national championship in team roping.

Early Career

In his early career, Milligan showcased his talent in various rodeos across the country. Despite the challenges of travel, he embraced the opportunity to meet new people and experience different towns.

His early successes included winning a rodeo in Vernon, Texas, and earning Rookie of the Year honors.

Professional Career

Tyler Milligan’s professional career began when he joined the Professional Rodeo Cowboys Association (PRCA) in 2016. His early career was marked by significant achievements, including winning the PRCA | Resistol Rookie of the Year in Tie-down Roping. 

Milligan’s career has been characterized by his dedication and skill, which have seen him qualify for the Wrangler National Finals Rodeo three times.

Tyler Milligan’s Net Worth in 2023

As of 2023, Tyler Milligan’s estimated net worth is $1 million. Milligan’s prime sources of earnings are his rodeo earnings and endorsements.

It’s important to note that net worth is not solely determined by career earnings but also includes assets like properties and investments, minus any debts.

Career Earnings

Tyler Milligan, a professional rodeo contestant, has had a fluctuating income over the years due to his performance in various rodeos. In 2017, he won the PRCA Tie-Down Roping Rookie of the Year title with an impressive $53,869 in season earnings. 

In 2020, he earned $60,919 on the season. He finished 45th in the world standings with $30,596, in 2021. However, in 2022, his regular season earnings were reported to be $118,708.
